rComments: One of the most instructive music profs in Toronto, enjoyed a great intro to comp. at UofT.
One of my favourite professors at U of T. He always makes the class interesting and easy to understand. He is also very helpful and caring.

Riotous analogies. His composition class pretty much makes up for the lack of PRACTICAL information provided by first year harmony classes if you need it (chart of proper chord progressions, etc). Amazingly hilarious and able to provide tons of down to earth information. Rewards innovation but gives you good marks if you go standard.
